OL,3,CCare minister says families barred
OL,4,Cfrom seeing disabled relatives is
OL,5,C'wrong'
OL,7,FThe Court of Protection is a
OL,8,Fspecialist court that determines
OL,9,Fwhether an individual has the mental
OL,10,Fcapacity to make decisions about their
OL,11,Fown health and welfare - many with
OL,12,Fsevere learning disabilities lack
OL,13,Fcapacity and are therefore referred to
OL,14,Fthe court.
OL,16,FCare Minister Stephen Kinnock said:
OL,17,F"It's very concerning and it's
OL,18,Fcompletely wrong. If families are
OL,19,Fbeing prevented from seeing their
OL,20,Floved ones, that is simply not
OL,21,Fallowed...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
